IDX Workbench Desktop Application

IDX Workbench is a desktop application that deploys OmniStudio data packs and Salesforce metadata. Its user interface is built on top of the OmniStudio Build Tool, available for Windows, Mac, and Linux.

Deployment is supported:

From one Vlocity org to another
From a Vlocity org to a Git repository
From a Git repository to a Vlocity org
From the Vlocity Process Library to a Vlocity org
From a JSON file to a Git repository or a Vlocity org

We recommend using the OmniStudio Build Tool for deploying OmniStudio components between orgs.

Components are packaged as data packs, optimized for source control and deployment to other orgs. For example, you can develop apps on a dedicated development org, deploy them to a QA org until ready for production, then deploy from QA to production orgs.

You can import data packs of some older OmniStudio for Vlocity objects into an OmniStudio Standard org. However, importing data packs of Standard objects into an OmniStudio for Vlocity org isn't supported.

When deploying components, IDX Workbench ensures dependent components are included. For example, if you deploy an OmniScript requiring a Data Mapper, that Data Mapper is packaged for deployment with the OmniScript.

To deploy changes to OmniStudio components, download and install the IDX Workbench application.

Before deploying components, specify the source, target, and objects to be deployed. The source can be an org, a Project object, a JSON file, the Vlocity Process Library, or a Git repository. The target can be an org or a Git repository.

After configuring a project, you can deploy objects from Source to Target. Compare objects in the Source and Target to see if any have been updated and need to be deployed again.

The IDX Workbench Process Profiler lets you view Tracking Service data for an object in a source or target org.
The Version Compare dashboard compares two versions of an OmniScript or Integration Procedure in the same Source or Target org.
The Test dashboard runs Test Procedures (Integration Procedures that perform unit tests) and analyzes results.

Importing data packs of some older objects into an OmniStudio Standard org is supported. 
OmniStudio Data Mapper, Integration Procedure, and LWC-enabled OmniScript custom objects are automatically converted to standard objects.

See Differences Between OmniStudio and OmniStudio for Vlocity.
